## 📋 Method Reference

| Method | Access | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `login(String password)` | `public` | Verifies password, starts session |
| `logout()` | `public` | Ends current session |
| `viewDashboard()` | `public` | Prints dashboard (common + role-specific) |
| `updateProfile(...)` | `public` | Updates username, bio, contact, password |
| `getRole()` | `public abstract` | Returns role label (implemented in subclass) |
| `displayRoleDashboard()` | `protected abstract` | Role-specific dashboard section |
| `onAccountRemoved()` | `public abstract` | Cleanup logic on account deletion |
| `setVerified(boolean)` | `protected` | Called by Admin to verify an account |
| `setBanned(boolean)` | `protected` | Called by Admin to ban/unban a user |

---

## ⚠️ Guard Conditions

Every method that modifies state or displays sensitive data checks two conditions before proceeding:

1. **`isLoggedIn()`** — Is there an active session?
2. **`isBanned()`** — Has this account been suspended?

If either condition fails, the method prints an appropriate message and returns early without performing any action.

---

## 🔗 Dependencies

`User.java` has **zero imports** from within the project. It is a pure base class that knows nothing about `Challenge`, `Submission`, or any service. This keeps the base class clean, testable, and decoupled from the rest of the system.

